The paper focuses on identifying potentially vulnerable locations in a code base, which is a software engineering problem (cs.SE). It also involves vulnerability assessment, which falls under computer security (cs.CR). The proposed framework, LEOPARD, is based on program metrics, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and system design (cs.SY). The paper mentions the use of machine learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
